replies.body:
Okay, here's an idea. What Riot could do is make a _game_ of out of it for _toxic_ players. Reformed or _Dead_. The focus of this game is not winning SR/TT or whatever mode they _get_. But its resisting the urge to snap back in kind to other toxic players. Of-course, to _play_ this game. Chat has to _remain_ unmuted for all of them. 

Basically, out of all the number of toxic players registered in a month. Only 0.5-1% of the least toxic ones get to retain their accounts while 99% get permanently banned. They could also make an entertaining stream out of it. Stream the last few games/moments of toxic players, showing off their account level along with the number of skins owned etc. before a certain phrase or string of sentences result in them getting _tilted_ so hard that they wind up responding in kind, and getting _insta. banned_. 

**Imagine**. A game where you end up winning _not_ because you are the most skilled. But because, you're the least toxic. The remaining 9 ended up getting banned and you were the only one left to finish off the Nexus! I'd chuckle watching this happen. Could be a temporary mode like URF for toxic players for a fixed amount of time! {{sticker:sg-syndra}}
